headline: EU sets Jan. 10 deadline for International Paper-DS Smith deal
summary: U.S.-based International Paper's 5.8-billion-pound ($7.29 billion) bid for British packaging firm DS Smith will be decided by EU antitrust regulators by Jan. 10, a European Commission filing showed on Tuesday. The deal, announced in April, would help International Paper expand its European presence at a time of consolidation in the sector. It sought EU approval on Monday.
